definition: variant of 歲|岁[sui4], year/years old
classifier for years (of age)/year/year (of crop harvests)
tip/end/final stage/latter part/inessential detail/powder/dust/opera role of old man

sentences.english: The end of the year, Jet Li's heart is still hanging.
sentences.chinese: 进入岁末，李连杰的心仍悬着。

sentences.english: It was my hope that we could balance the budget before the year is out.

sentences.english: The White House South Lawn witnessed waving national flags of China and US in the air of near-year-end Washington.

sentences.english: He said as the year is coming to an end the domestic work schedule is fairly busy.
sentences.chinese: 他说，时近岁末，国内各项工作十分繁忙。

sentences.english: Year-end months lock yourself in the home, will experience into a poem encouraged.
